description: One of the Firestarter cabins carried across the Wasteland by the night itself.

name: Shiv ST
description: Take a look at the original wheel rim design. It brings out the sharp emotions of driving across the Wasteland. The faster you drive, the more it hurts for those hit by the spikes! Each mounted wheel reduces cabin power.

name: Shiv
description: Take a look at the original wheel rim design. It brings out the sharp emotions of driving across the Wasteland. The faster you drive, the more it hurts for those hit by the spikes! Each mounted wheel reduces cabin power.

name: Fire Salamander
description:
Spray Can.
Can colour most parts.

name: Capricorn
description: Stickers can be placed on any surface, as well rotated and changed in size.

name: Phoenix
description:
A simple crossbow wasn't enough for Firestarter engineers, so they added a bit of explosives.
The projectile sticks to the enemy hull and after a few seconds deals significant damage during the explosion. But if the victim or its allies have time to destroy the projectile while the wick is burning, then detonation will not happen.

name: Bigfoot ST
description: Saved from the time of the competitions of giant trucks and was improved by Firestarters to crush the enemies more effectively. Each mounted wheel reduces cabin power.

name: Bigfoot
description: Saved from the time of the competitions of giant trucks and was improved by Firestarters to crush the enemies more effectively. Each mounted wheel reduces cabin power.

name: Oppressor
description:
An armored car with an extremely powerful 12-valve engine that can blow away everything in its path: small obstacles, sleepy raiders, a roof...

Only one engine can be installed on the vehicle.

name: Werewolf
description: With a cabin like this, a defeat can turn into a victory! And it does not fear silver bullets.

name: Tormentor
description: With this hardware, all melee weapons start to spin like crazy and hurt everyone even more for $spell_duration$ sec.

name: Draco
description: This used to be an agricultural flamethrower for destruction of weeds and pests. A rare case, when the essence has not changed over time.

name: Fortune
description:
Launches three wheels, which roll happily and explode when they collide with an enemy or receive damage.
They are stuffed with unstable explosives, so they detonate after 8 sec.

name: Incinerator
description: Launches an incendiary projectile, that leaves a burning area at the place of explosion. When you hit someone with this weapon, Firestarters scream, it seems, something about a fiery hyena. Apparently, they do not know that they are not found in Wasteland.

name: Stallion ST
description: Pneumatic suspension with variable ride height allows the car to operate in two modes. And also perform tricks.

name: Jockey
description: Despite a somewhat awkward appearance and many patches on the hood, this cabin can pleasantly surprise you.

name: Stallion
description: Pneumatic suspension with variable ride height allows the car to operate in two modes. And also perform tricks.

name: Lollipop
description:
Spray Can.
Can colour most parts.

name: Ambulance lights
description: A box of lights with a siren, miraculously preserved after the disaster, alerting everyone around that they need to give way urgently.

name: Hot Rod
description:
A classic that has lived through dozens of modifications, perfect for surviving tough conditions in style.

A multi-purpose cabin with good speed and small size.

name: Plague
description:
Spray Can.
Can colour most parts.

name: With the shield or on the shield
Tusk
description: Several tusks fixed on this cabin's front are not only an element of intimidation, but also an unusual melee weapon.

name: Boar scalp
description:
Spray Can.
Can colour most parts.

name: Missile balloons
description: Inflatable Missiles is a great way to make fun of your friends.

name: Inflatable Mammoth
description: The inflatable cannon was conceived as a decoy gadget. But its ridiculous appearance made it incredibly popular in the Wasteland.

name: Royal trophy
description: This prestigious award can only be received by winning in Battle Royale.

name: Cyclone
description: An arms race often becomes the engine of progress. Who would have thought that you could squeeze out additional firepower from a twin auto-cannon. But it happened. Moreover, Cyclone's rate of fire rises while shooting!

name: Goliath
description:
People have invented similar tracks during their first global war with each other. Now they are used in the current, less global war.
When mounted, severely limit the car's maximum speed. Each mounted track reduces the cabin's power.

name: M-37 Piercer
description: Machine gun with extreme rate of fire and a burst fire mode. Don't expect pinpoint accuracy and huge damage, but it can provide surprising density of fire.

name: Prometheus V
description: It's amazing how ideas of inventions come almost simultaneously to different people. The creators of Prometheus V, although they had worked independently, assembled a weapon very reminiscent of Synthesis. Each shot boosts the next one.

name: Fafnir
description:
The engineer in charge of this metal monster's design was clearly inspired by legends of dragons.
A volley from a couple of these shotguns can literally vaporise anyone who's foolish enough to stand too close.

name: Aspect
description: This machine gun requires nerves of steel to deal maximum damage. But with sufficient gunner skill it's unparalleled at medium distances.

name: Solomon's pattern
description:
Spray Can.
Can colour most parts.

name: Ghost
description: Once this cabin belonged to a helicopter and climbed high in the sky. It's just as hard to believe, as the fact that TVs kill people. However, all of this is true.

name: Kapkan
description:
A curious weapon with mines that won't let a single victim elude you.
Does not affect trucks and leviathans.

name: Mentor's container
description: Contains decor parts not available anywhere else.

name: Misty Marshes
description:
Paint and patterns.
Can colour most parts.

name: Vuvuzela
description: A ringing blast to accompany every match ever and, of course, the post-game celebrations.

name: To the championship!
description: Spray paint and pattern in the style of “Steel Championship”. Can be applied to most parts.

name: Torero
description: This cabin from a powerful supercar is equipped with a mighty engine and a couple of tech solutions increasing accuracy.

name: Corno sinistro
description: The owner of this decoration is easy to find because of the unique twin flames ejected by the pipes.

name: Corno destro
description: The owner of this decoration is easy to find because of the unique twin flames ejected by the pipes.

name: Muleta Wing
description: A wing of this shape attracts everyone's attention and occasionally bullets from haters.

name: El Dorado
description:
Spray Can.
Can colour most parts.

name: Half-light
description:
Spray Can.
Can colour most parts.

name: Contact 2M
description:
Want to shoot some targets with a friend, but he keeps driving away?
Just couple his vehicle to yours!
You and your ally should both install the module “Contact 2M”, activate it and get the crafts as close together as possible. One module can only be used to attach to a single vehicle.

name: Corvo
description:
Looks very much like a gun from the very old world, when the knechte were far from roaming the Wasteland's highways. It very well may be that there were no highways at all (such savagery!).
Ammunition reserves and reloading speed can't be changed. The clip is reloaded automatically.

name: Nidhogg
description:
Deliberate, yet lethal force that's fit to sing songs about.
The shotgun reaches its peak efficiency at close range and high speed.

name: Helios
description: Allegedly, the early prototypes of this emitter were very unstable and took the lives of at least as many allies as they did enemies. But does all this really matter if it launches a volley of 5 plasma pellets, deals high damage and has incredible accuracy?

name: Oculus VI
description:
This Dawn's Children prototype was “borrowed” by Scavengers. The module turns towards the hidden enemy, blinks and beeps. With this gadget, nobody else can take you by surprise!
Invisibility detection range up to $detection_radius$ m.
Enemy detection range up to $radar_radius$ m.

name: Fleur-de-lis
description:
Paint and patterns.
Can colour most parts.

name: Skull pipe
description: This trophy from the “Witch Hunt” should come in handy, plus it's always going to laugh at your jokes.

name: Mummy
description:
Spray Can.
Can colour most parts.

name: Favorite
description:
A prototype stolen straight from the factory and amateurishly modified a couple of times to take part in illegal races.

A versatile cabin with good speed.

name: Braid
description: This exhaust was build quick and dirty. Anything and everything was used to make it as rad as possible, even a motorcycle frame for the support structure. This explains the part's... twisty nature.

name: Topper
description: A lightweight fender molding.

name: Eggplant
description:
Spray Can.
Can colour most parts.

name: M-38 Fidget
description: Twin-barrel rapid-fire machine gun. Commonly used by Steppenwolfs in quick Wasteland skirmishes, where you always need to be quick on your wheels.

name: M-39 Imp
description: This innovative Steppenwolf weapon boasts very high rate of fire and deadly damage. Used for setting up mobile ambushes to destroy parts of hostile armored vehicles at short range extremely quickly.

name: Donut
description: This decor part looks like a target and often attracts unwanted attention. But the harder the battle, the sweeter the victory!

name: Twin spare
description: When an old tyre can no longer serve its original purpose, you can use it to build a lot of original decorations. Or you can just stick it on your car.

name: Spiked spare
description: When an old tyre can no longer serve its original purpose, you can use it to build a lot of original decorations. Or you can just stick it on your car.

name: Big spare
description: When an old tyre can no longer serve its original purpose, you can use it to build a lot of original decorations. Or you can just stick it on your car.
